# OpenClaw Bridge

An autonomous OpenClaw agent periodically reviews this repository and writes
task suggestions to `.cursor/openclaw-bridge/inbox.jsonl`.

## When to check

At the start of a session, or when the user mentions "bridge", "openclaw",
or "inbox", read `.cursor/openclaw-bridge/inbox.jsonl` and look for lines
where `"status":"pending"`.

## inbox.jsonl format

Each line is a JSON object:

```
{"id":"task-001","ts":"...","type":"task","priority":"high","title":"...","prompt":"...","status":"pending"}
```

- `status: "pending"` -- not yet picked up
- `status: "done"` -- already completed

## How to handle tasks

1. Read all pending tasks from inbox.jsonl.
2. Present them to the user as a summary (title + priority).
3. Only execute a task if the user explicitly confirms it.
4. After completing a task, append a result line to `.cursor/openclaw-bridge/outbox.jsonl`:

```
{"id":"task-001","ts":"...","type":"result","summary":"...","files_changed":["..."],"status":"done"}
```

5. Do NOT auto-execute tasks without user approval.
6. Do NOT modify inbox.jsonl -- only append to outbox.jsonl.

## Goal document

The agent's strategic goals are in `.cursor/openclaw-bridge/goal.md`.
Read it for context on priorities and direction when evaluating tasks.
